headline: This Couple Oversees Billions in Assets. We Caught Up With Them.
summary: Rogers is executive co-chairman of  Hamilton Lane  a global private markets asset manager.  Falls is chief investment officer at Northwestern University.  At Northwestern, Falls manages an endowment of roughly $15 billion, of which she says private assets make up about half.
